<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by AppleKid on 04-21-2001 02:42 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> If you're playing with the button art, here's a little trick I used to do on my C64 to simulate semi-transparent. Make every other pixel "transparent"... you know, that ungodly ugly purple that's treated as clear... the one that was just recently fixed on dropped coins   :) ... Just like a checkerboard drop it on the spell gem. I'm fairly sure one could get PSP5+ to do some paper tricks to make it easier to paint.

 It'll look like ass at low resolutions (unless you've got a cheap monitor, heh heh) but should be pretty acceptable at 1024x768.

 The only problem would be if clicking on a "clear" pixel wouldn't count as clicking on the gem. Hmmm... it's about time I start contributing... I've got a weekend project.

Update: Game seems to crash just before the character select screen. A manual CRC check done? *shrug* Bug in eqinside? I don't think that's likely. If you wanna d/l the spellgems and try it yourself, perhaps with better luck, download this PNG [and remember to save as a BMP before importing... 77k vs 900k...] http://members.tripod.com/~SemantiKat/spelgems.png

[This message has been edited by AppleKid (edited 04-22-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
